metadata.name: Smile_Bamboo #23
metadata.description:
From within a single acupuncture point, a trunk stretches out, like a bamboo, in a straight line and at different angles.

One leaf. And one round fruit.
It is like a smile, the one we are always looking for.

A smile is what I seek from day to day.
Just a straight, pure smile.

I felt as if I would lose such a natural expression as a human being at any moment.

I began to wish for a code, a number to smile at me again.

I can't draw faces in sketches well.
But I enjoyed reloading over and over again, hoping to find a smile somewhere in the randomness of this code.


May the world be filled with smiles.
That is all I pray for.

Asahamiz

metadata.name: lineJag_aliasing #18
metadata.description:
The jaggies created by the lines create smooth noise.
Are they pretending not to notice, or are they really invisible? There is not a single line that is truly loose.
I really want to find evidence that no line is loose.
But I keep finding it and hiding it, then finding it and hiding it.
Still, I feel a little fear and respect for the fact that the straight line connecting "somewhere" and "somewhere" is built on the trust that they are connected, when they are not really connected.

metadata.name: Midfile Crisis #230
metadata.description:
Midfile Crisis is about realizing halfway through you are not gonna make it.

The struggle is real.

-

The work itself is the union of 2 projects, which, well, didn’t make it. Together though, they are stronger than ever. So yes, Midfile Crisis is a love story, too.

-

Procedural , ever changing real-time animation, October 2022
Javascript and WebGL

-

FEATURES

- 6 color palettes, inspired by recent artworks by Xenia Hausner, Ayako Rokkaku, Jenny Saville, Amy Sherald, Sue Williams and Emily Xie, are referenced accordingly. One additional, rare color palette will slowly cycle through the full color spectrum.
- Direction: Up, Right, Up Right
- Seed: Up, Right, Up Left
- Shape Tendency: Tetra, Box, Sphere, Octa, Ico, Multi
- Amount: Low, Medium, High

VIEWING

- The artwork is in landscape format, please click on open to see the full frame and resolution. We recommend rotating your screen on mobile.
- Press 'i' to show artwork title and features.
- Press 's' to save an image.
- To guarantee the same output at different resolutions the simulation driving the artwork is locked at 1024x512 pixels. To unlock, press 'u' - this can help when running at a lower resolution and the animation is not smooth, or when running at significanly higher resolutions and pixelation is starting to occur. Please note this will break the deterministic nature of the work.
- Best viewed in Chrome Desktop with dedicated GPU.
- Please note: requires latest devices (supporting WebGL2) for a smooth experience.

metadata.name: The Sprawl #24
metadata.description:
The sprawl. A shimmering maze of light and beauty. A living, breathing, churning mess thrown into chaos by a long forgotten runtime exception. Automaton ghosts operate on hard-coded rulesets, grasping to understand the zero-player game in which they are trapped. Individuals are lost to the great invisible broken machine as exponential memory leaks spin out endless reconfigurations, expanding and expanding for a momentary glimpse at a fraction of reality.

@d0n.xyz

metadata.name: in between #10
metadata.description:
A land where all opposites meet and come together, everything is interconnected, interdependent and in a state of constant change and transformation, far away from here.

Although “in between” is first and foremost an image composition project, it uses different generative techniques to emulate analog film behaviour.

By adding "&date=YYYY-MM-DD" to the URL you can go to a specific date.

metadata.name: Let Me Paint #47
metadata.description:
“Let Me Paint” is a computer’s request to create a painting, abstract expressionism in this case, which machines can’t do, since they cannot have feelings.
On the other hand, this is my own request to myself. The request to do what you want, without thinking much about whether it will bring any benefit (in any sense) to me or others.
In an effort to do anything with some profit in the future, I have driven myself into these thoughts. And even now I “draw” using a computer, hiding it behind a wall of code to make it look reasonable (to me).

——————

To change the size of the image, open it in live view and add ‘&size=[size (6400 max.)]’ to the end of the URL.
To render a version without grain add ‘&grain=false’ to the end of the URL.

Controls:
[S] — save the image.

Created with p5.js and GLSL.
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.

——————

hrunz. — Jan. 2023.

metadata.name: Inner Chaos #191
metadata.description:
Inner Chaos is about my personal struggles with anxiety and fear. Through this artwork, I attempt to visually represent the complex and often overwhelming emotions that I experience on a daily basis. It is a reflection of the cyclical nature of my thoughts and feelings, and the ways in which I try to make sense of them. But as I delve deeper into my own personal experiences, I realize that in the end, internal chaos should not be controlled, but accepted.

This artwork is my most personal, as it reflects my innermost sensations. It is a reminder to myself and to others that it is okay to not have everything under control, and that it is important to allow the uncertainty and unpredictability of life. I hope that it will resonate with others and provide a sense of connection and understanding. It is a reminder that we are not alone in our struggles and that it is important to embrace our own imperfections.


Please use fullscreen or download artwork in high resolution for a better viewing experience. Chrome is highly recommended for high res saving.

Made with love and p5js.


Controls in fullscreen:
[1] - save PNG 1200 x 1800
[2] - save PNG 2400 x 3600
[3] - save PNG 4800 x 7200
[4] - save PNG 7200 x 10800

On mobile:
[quick tap] - save PNG

metadata.name: Dreamscape #4
metadata.description:
As I create each artwork, my interest in circular patterns grows, so this is an exploration of combining nested circular algorithms with linear patterns. A wide variety of sizes and color palettes have been considered for this artwork.  This artwork can also be plotted in large dimensions.
_________________________

To see the artwork in high quality, open it in live view and add “&res=1 to 25” to the URL.

Made with p5js.
